snippet.textDisplay: Sorry just had to comment on the "attachment parenting" thing, I was raised this way just kind of on accident and I like continuously cite it as the reason I am so close with my parents and why I was such a "good kid". Mostly with my dad because he was older and had less going on in life at the time, but I was his little buddy attached at the hip always. Not to "toot my own horn" or anything because it could just be family hyping me up, but I am consistently told how good of a toddler and youth I was and how people didn't feel like they were ever "stuck with me" because I was just always used to hanging around adults alone and having to keep myself busy or try and conversate with them. I'm sure yall already know that its a good fit for your family, but I just wanted to offer my 2c as a child that was raised that way.

snippet.textDisplay: The concept is overall really nice BUT here are my thoughts: candy/sweet bar area needed more light!. They could’ve added strawberries dipped in chocolate or something like that to add more of a luxurious touch to it, light marble floors and counter tops would’ve been better. I wouldn’t have kept the green old tiles either. It didn’t seem like Jeffrey liked the face, that zen room is too plain and empty. The massage room had enough space to add 2 beds! All the other rooms are quite empty. The massage room was sort of over decorated compared to the rest. I would’ve replaced the fireplace for something more modern, same for the jacuzzi.
